<Rating>1</Rating>< text>
This place will steal your money if you try to pay with your card inside!!!!! They got me for $9.99 after telling me my card was declined and to run it as credit (which was also declined). However, at the pump, my card worked just fine. When i noticed my pending transactions later that same day, i returned to the store and tried talking to the employee who had helped me. She started ranting and raving that I was out to get her when i asked to see the copies of both declined receipts as she had only given me one. She then proceeded to take the reeceipts out laying them down one by one. Right before the decline which i had a copy for, i noticed the previous receipt was for $9.99. I asked to see the receipt to make sure it wasn't an accidental charge and this employee flipped out. I will never go here again. A few months back the same incident happened to my roommate, same gas station but different employee. They got her for $30. It seems that this is acceptable employee practices and behavior to this Valero owner, shame on you!!!!!</text>

He was the perfect ‚ÄúPapa Duck‚Äù.

I don‚Äôt remember if there‚Äôs options but I wouldn‚Äôt do anything less than a 2 hour tour (if it‚Äôs an option). You don‚Äôt get too wet but you are on the water, so bathing suit and appropriate over clothes and sun screen would be perfect. < username>
Cory Beal< /username>
<rate>5< /rate>< Review>
What an incredible morning we had for my wife‚Äôs birthday, with our tour guide Captain Scott. Two hour tour (about 90 mins on the water) and you are in total control. Think of it like horseback riding on speedboats.

On the tour you get to open it up full throttle and chop through the waves, passing Navy Vessels and the San Diego skyline. Highlights, besides the speed, was passing the USS Lincoln aircraft carrier, seeing live sea lions play in your boat wake, driving right next to and under the USS Midway, and our guide Scott.

We were lucky enough to have the tour all to ourselves at 11:00am on a Monday and Scott was awesome and personal. He made us feel comfortable and capable and driving the speedboats is easy no matter your experience level. Amazing day on the water and money completely well spent!

Tips: 1. You do NOT get wet so don‚Äôt worry about that, dress for weather. 2. Bring cash for a tip (Scott deserves it in these times) 3. Sunscreen on hot days there is no shade unless you count the Midway!<//Review>

< review>
First off, I had trouble on the website and Chris was quick to respond to my email and help me out.

This adventure was exactly as advertised.  Our guide Scott let us know before we left the dock what to expect, what the water was going to be like, and how to maneuver the boat during choppy waters. We had a great time and would definitely book another adventure with this company.</review>

< review>
My wife and I bought the Go San Diego card and we're trying to find something to do one of the mornings and decided to give this a try. We absolutely loved it. Looking back on our trip in the airport we actually felt like this was the most enjoyable thing we did while we were in San Diego. For those of you who are wondering how it works, we called and made a reservation for the next morning, which was really easy, filled out some waivers online, showed up the next morning and got to drive our own little speed motor boats on a tour around the harbor. It was such an awesome experience. We loved our guide Ryan, and everything we got to see and experience while out driving our own boats! You absolutely should sign up for this if you buy a Go San Diego card, even if you don't have the card, I'd highly recommend this tour!<//review>

<user_id>102044899160219104765</user_id><Name>Kevin Yeoman< /Name><date>1572204726022< /date><rating>5</rating>< review>
The highlight of our day. This tour was exactly what we wanted, informative and entertaining narrative as we explored the bay, and between stops the thrill of racing along the waves. We've done this twice, and my wife and I both think it is a great value.

The staff is energetic and friendly, safety conscious and entertaining. The entire business is the kind that you want to see successfull.

Calm days are great for families and kids, but if you want a real thrill, go when its windy. The larger waves mean a thrilling ride that would put most rollercoasters to shame. Some boats are faster then others, but I'm not telling, this way I can keep them to myself when I come back!

Wish I could give 10 stars.</review>

Such a FUN way to see the city!  My husband and I have spent a little time on boats so we were super excited to do this tour.  Having our own speed boat to play around with in the bay sounded like the perfect way to spend an afternoon.  We did the 3pm tour which was the perfect time of day ‚Äì not too hot!  You get a quick lesson and overview of what you will see then you head out on the boats.  Its about a 2 hour tour around the bay and worth EVERY penny.  Our guide was Jason and he was fantastic ‚Äì very fun as well as knowledgeable about boats and the San Diego.   If you have two people that want to drive, you can switch ¬Ω way through.  This is a great activity for people visiting San Diego, or even San Diego natives like us!</Text>

<Review>Terrible experience. We bought san diego go card from costco and this was one of the attractions we looked forward to do, however, it turned out to be a nightmare for me and my wife. We did this on Jun 30, 9 am. It was fine for first 30 minutes or so and all of a sudden our boat stopped working and we were left stranded in the middle of the ocean for more than 45 minutes. We did everything. We gave the distress signs, whistled to get the guides attention but in vain. He did not spot us because he sped off,  as a guide he should have made sure everyone are following before he took off or atleast stay in the middle so he can spot every rider. We called the office and she tried to reach the guide and in the meantime our boat was driven by the ocean winds as the steering does not work. It was SCARY!! It took the guide 45 minutes to spot us and rather than being appologetic we were shocked when he had asked us how we ended up here. The wind dragged the boat to other end of the ocean. We were so excited to do this but it turned out to be a "LOST" adventure. I will not be recommending this to my friends and family. The guide should always keep track of the riders. Period!! Unable to locate us for almost 45 minutes in the middle of ocean is unacceptable.<//Review><pictures>None<//pictures>< response>

< Resp>

<name>Nadja Volkmer</name>< time>
1483471166746<//time>
< GmapID>
0x80deab6b310efb73:0x92512bd5733c94d9</GmapID>
< userid>
109782127815804642280<//userid>
<Pictures>None</Pictures><Rate>1<//Rate>< Review>
Everything is fine, until something goes wrong. Your guide will loose its temper, shout and yell at you and at the end, he left us alone. Frustrating. Irresponsible. And for sure unprofessional and a no-go for this price.
1. If you are taller than 6', we cannot recommend this tour. We have bruises all over our knees.
2. If the two people in the boat are heavier than 400 lbs, we cannot recommend this. You will have to push your weight to the front of the boat for getting it "on plane", which basically means to get speed. In the beginning you will have additional weight of the full gas tank in the front to get you going. But at the end of the tour, your weight will not be enough to push down the nose of the boat and you will never get "on plane" anymore. The Guide (Bob or Rob) will make you keep trying, but if you have any understanding of physics, it is simply not possible anymore because of your weight and the mass distribution. Usually boats have a trim to adjust the motor to this weight distribution. But these boats are simple and small and don't have it or the guide didn't tell or know about it.
3. We had rather big waves. This also interrupts the traction to the water, which doesn't allow you to get speed. We ended up trying and failing.

The thing is, this trip is not a sightseeing tour. Don't expect that. You will be busy getting control over your boat and to follow the guide. He is alone in his boat and way ahead of you. They do not offer a two-way radio, there is only a speaker in the boat and while you are standing, leaning over the bow to get on plane, you will not hear a single word he says. After we mentioned this to him, he simply said "I know". How helpful is that? There are not even hand signals agreed on to have a minimum of communication with the guide.

When stopped the 2nd time, he told us that because of our problems in the beginning there will be no stop on the tour anymore. He more or less blamed us to ruin the tour for everybody else. Honestly, we didn't wanted to stop anymore and just go back. But guess what... Of course he stopped again, I ignored him first and got yelled at me again over the intercom... So I stopped and never got the boat on plane again. We were lying on the bow for the rest of the tour. Our knees hurt, our back and neck hurt. The guide was annoyed, rude and not helpful at all. If someone is yelling at you, that "nobody ever had these problems", I can tell you to read Yelp. There a dozens of reviews stating the same problems and the same carelessness. It was frustrating and nothing, we will recommend.

It might be a lot of fun, if you get speed. But there a a lot of factors, that could prevent you to get "on plane". And if so, it is no fun at all. The guide is not prepared for this situation and you might end up paying a lot of money for bad service.</Review>

Sorry....this review is for nail bar.
I tried to remove this from here but I cannot.

I wanted to cry today 12/3o/17 after she was done with my nails.

Kim the owner is very gifted, talented smart young woman who unfortunately is letting making more money  getting on the way of providing good services.

I have been in Nai Bar 2 times and both times my nails were done by kim the owner.

The first time I went the one located in Windsor on 10/2017. The day I went I was looking for some one to take me in without an appointment....and my hair dresser recommended her....She said appointment are not needed there. My hairdresser called and She confirmed that the owner kim will be doing my acrylic nails and the design colors I wanted.
Kim did for the most part all the work and had her staff helped her finalzing the acrylics part . I asked her to do the nail design. She did.
I showed her the picture of the design of nails upon my arrival..she came back with the colors. My only bad experience that day was at the very end...when she attempted to send me away without finishing the design because more people was coming in and She wanted to take care of them..I pointed out to her that I was feeling rushed....(she said we were done and She did not finish painting the last part of the design). I asked her to finish the job nicely.
She did not like my comment.
She asked that cashier to add 20 dollars more for the design. I did not mind as long as the job was done properly. I paid 50 dollars for acrylic nails with gel and 20 for the design. I did not mind paying 70 dollars because the nails ended up beautiful!
The second time I did my nails was today, 12/30/2017. I went to her store in Petaluma. This time I called ahead of time to make an appointment hoping I will be able to have more relax time....I did not want to feel rush.
I was told to go there at 1pm. I was approached by her receptionist asking me to pick the colors while I was waiting. I told her that I would but wanted Kim input as an  artist to make sure I pick the correct colors as the picture. Kim started her work at 2 15 pm

She is pregnant....and a baby inside of her is exposed to chemicals. I made a comment to wear a mask to protect her unborn baby from inhaling those chemicals... and She ignored my comment.
She was so rude and unkind.
She will see her own karma.</review>

<UserId.>101366803884821235766< /UserId.><text>The very first thing I rate a Mexican establishment on, is it's salsa. Chips came with red and green salsa and a small plate of spiced chilled cabbage which I'd never seen served before. It was warm outside and I found the cabbage very refreshing. The green salsa was mild, had a deep robust flavor and was awesome!  The red salsa was ok. Nothing special, although someone in our party said it wasn't nearly as spicy as it usually was and didn't taste the same, so maybe they were just having an off day with it. The food was good and our waiter was wonderful. Someone in our party wanted a strawberry margarita but they were out of strawberries. Yet in 20 minutes, here came a wonderful frozen strawberry margarita! Our waiter had sent someone to the store for strawberries. Now THAT is service! All in all, i would definitely recommend La Hacienda Grill. I'm going to withhold opinion on the red salsa until I try it again. Yes, I'm going back!</text>< Date>

<Date>1583427755786< /Date><rate>5</rate>< Text>
The Crowne Plaza in Palo Alto was a wonderful place to stay.  My husband had surgery at Stanford so we chose the hotel based on proximity to the hospital.  They offer a discounted rate if you are at Stanford hospital (call ahead and let them know), the restaurant is very good, breakfast buffet is awesome and the room service is excellent.  We had a quiet room at the back of the hotel and very comfortable bedding for restful sleep after the hospital stay.  The entire staff was friendly and extremely helpful and kind.  They even had a wheelchair for our use as it was too far for my husband to walk after being discharged.  They are also ideally located for anything you might need - pharmacy, restaurants, etc.  I highly recommend them!</Text>

I choose this hotel of its vicinity to Stanford University. We attended Family Week at Stanford and it made travelling to all the events easy to attend. We checked in late Friday afternoon and our room was available in the 8th floor as per my preference. A staff member knocked on our door and offered us bottled water and candy for IHG members. Would definitely stay at this Crown Plaza when we attend another event at Stanford University in the future.</Review>

<date>1565740800000<//date><Rating>None< /Rating>< review>
I found the staff at this IHG/Crowne Plaza Hotel exceptional. From the front desk, restaurant/bar wait staff, housekeeping and maintenance.....everyone was extremely polite and courteous. For example, if a staff member was toting laundry to another location and saw that a guest was on the elevator, the staff wouldn't board. I've been to other hotels where staff viewed their task more important than the comfort of a guest. I saw a number of times, staff wiping down walls and thoroughly cleaning the elevators and common areas. It seems to me that either someone is doing a very good job of recruiting the right people or the staff are trained very well.< /review>

< Text>
Initially, I was disappointed upon check-in. I frequently book this suite because the whirlpool aids in the treatment of a severed nerve from a leg injury. I expect mediocre conditions when I choose a hotel based on price, but I have observed diminishing conditions during my annual stay here over the last three years that make this hotel a poor choice for a business traveler. Stained curtains, too few healthy menu items, always something wrong with my room, no one picks up room service trays overnight. This year the power went out at 6 am across the whole hotel and there was no effort made to check in with or advise guests. When I checked out at 8:30 am (power still out), no one even mentioned it until I asked what happened! I will say the staff is friendly even if not impressive and the beds are comfortable, so if the power stays on, this hotel is doable for a budget traveler if you don‚Äôt need more than that.< /text>

<Review>This hotel has a touch of class. I was exhausted upon entering the hotel. Wasn't sure where to park but we came through the lobby and went up to check in. Check in was easy. My boyfriend was still hungry and ended up buying a soup. Unfortunately, there was no place to heat it up although I think he eventually found something. I came up and unpacked. Jumped in the shower and got ready to relax. I noticed the eucalyptus package of spray and massage creme, How nice, I thought. I sprayed the pillow and decided to play a little music. The music was all so relaxing. Unusual and just what I needed. My boyfriend jumped in the shower. I was so thrilled to have the massage creme. I was able to use the massage creme to rub his back and feet and off to sleep we went. It was really nice. A wonderful treat. The next day I took my time and went down for breakfast. I'm looking for a place to live in the area. I also had lunch the next day and invited a friend. We loved the food and the service was excellent. The room was so relaxing and I loved the little room where the Christmas tree was by the television although I wasn't able to sit there. All you need is a fire pit outside and a couple of nice chairs to lounge in. My only suggestion is to buy a couple of new flags outside. they were all ripped. I loved this hotel and my guest room was beautifully decorated in warm colors. If you had more television stations that would be even better. I loved my stay and will definitely be back! I'm planning a trip in February 2016 and I've already recommended this hotel to a friend of mine. Thank you for making this trip so nice. It is a great memory of an early Christmas in 2015! I stay at many hotels during the course of any year and I can honestly say I have never experienced such a positive team spirit at any of them compared to this Crowne Plaza. From top to bottom nothing was too much trouble and the little touches like the free local transport and wine and cheese sessions made the hotel a delight to stay at.

< text>
I stayed here two nights on a business trip.  The staff were exceedingly courteous and kind. I enjoyed their wine and cheese tasting in the evening, and loved that they had water available throughout the day in the lobby.   The grounds were lovely and my room comfortable.  However, the bed was very firm (okay if you like that), and the room could use some maintenance.  But other than that - very comfortable and well-appointed.  The breakfast buffet was solidly good - lots of fresh fruit, oatmeal with lots of options for toppings, bacon, eggs, pancakes/french toast, various pastries.  Nice, but not extravagant.  Overall - I felt the price was a bit high for what I got - however, all the hotels were quite expensive in the area at this time.</text>

< text>
When making the reservation, we chose the "Poolside cabana Kingsize" room, which on the website was the only room with no photo available. These rooms appear to be in the oldest part of the hotel, and are showing some signs of age. Most importantly, I would expect a "Poolside cabana" room to have access to the pool. This is NOT the case. There is a tiny patio where you can see the pool, and a giant Iron railing that prevents one from getting to the pool area; hence one must exit into the hallway, walk all of the way to the end of the wing, into the hotel lobby then back out and again around another 100 feet to get to the pool. Having recent back surgery i thought the spa might be nice, but the foot travel to get there and back prevented me from attempting to use it.</text>

<userid>None< /userid><Name>Rit08</Name><Time>1523750400000<//Time>< Rating>
None<//Rating>
<text>I had stayed in several Crowne Plaza hotels hence when I thought of a hotel to go to with my husband for our 10th year anniversary, this was what I suggested. The experience was okay and I really appreciated the kindness and attention to detail of one of the waiters at the dining. However on our last morning, my husband and I got down around 10am for breakfast and we were told breakfast was over, it was time for brunch and we will have to pay for the brunch (breakfast was included in our reservation). The employees at the dining area did well to explain to me and said I was supposed to have been told at the time of check in. They offered to refund us $2 for the breakfast and to pay for only 1 person's meal for the brunch but since my husband and I were not yet ready for something heavy, we decided to proceed with our plans for the morning. 

Upon check out I spoke to a lady at the frontdesk and she said two things that shocked me. First of all that she was sure that the person who checked me in must have told me about the rules of breakfast and secondly if I did not get it, either I was not listening or my mind was not there. I found it very rude that an employee at the frontdesk could make such a statement to a customer. She was not there when I was checked in hence she cannot conclude that the person who checked me in indeed told me (and my husband) about the rules of breakfast. To even suggest that I was either not listening or my mind was not there was even worse because both my husband and I can verify that the person who checked us in did not mention anything about breakfast.

I have always enjoyed my experience at Crowne Plaza hotels but this experience has made me reconsider whether I will use personal funds for a future stay at Crowne Plaza hotels.

My recommendations however will be:-
1. Let employees be retrained on customer service. One of the waiters is a fantastic example of how people should treat customers.
2. Have hardcopy information about the rules of breakfast somewhere such that if those at the frontdesk miss it, guests can read about it in their rooms or somewhere else.<//text>< Pics>
None<//Pics>
< Resp>
None<//Resp>

< Review>
I'm not a big hotel person because I am very picky when it comes to cleanliness.  This hotel was probably the BEST experience I have ever had in hotels. There was nothing I could say that was wrong with my stay here.


Unfortunately I was not there for business or pleasure.  Palo Alto is home of Stanford Medical Center, so I was staying at Crowne Plaza while my mother was battling for her life. It was a huge comfort to come back to the hotel after my long days at the hospital.

The staff in this hotel went above and beyond their duties to make sure I was comfortable.  Everywhere I went I was met with a caring face.  From the courtesy shuttle to and from the hospital, to the food service, bar and lounge  It was all excellent!
There was one particular individual and I wish I would have gotten her name. She would greet me every morning as the host of the food lounge.  She read my body language and knew something was wrong.  She stayed with me at the table while I cried and didn't leave my side until she felt I was ok.  Now thats an angel!  I don't know if I will ever see her again, but I would really like her to know the impact she had on me that morning.  My mother died the next day.

This entire hotel employs quality people who really care.  I can't say enough about my stay here. I would definitely come and stay here again.</Review>

< text>
Fantastic experience, hands-down.
Due to other reviews on this property, I was 50/50 before checking-in. And after two-nights, I am 100% a fan!

At this quiet college town, this is a BIG hotel property.
Full service bar, and HUGE dinning area.
The room is clean, and the bathroom is spacious.

At this property, though, I had to fill out paperwork in the same way that anyone that didn't have a reservation would need to, even though all of that same information is also in my IHG profile (which they acknowledged they had access to). What should have been a 2-3 minute check-in process turned into a 20 minute debacle where a staff member clearly under training tried to get this done.

Check-out brought more of the same. No bill under my door as normal, so I had to go to the front desk to get a copy of the bill. Again, what is normally a 1-2 minute print out took over 20 minutes to get done.

Maybe when the staff is fully trained, this hotel will be worth staying at. Until this, I'd stay away for a bit until that is resolved<//text>< Pictures>

<review>I booked and paid for an executive king suite but was informed on check-in (11pm) that there had been a "cancellation issue" with my room and I was offered either a standard king or a Cabana 2-queen room as an alternative. The explanation given as to how this could have happened was very vague and noncommittal -- but let's be real: I booked a particular room and they either rented it to someone else (their mistake) or perhaps it experienced a secret maintenance issue that could not be resolved (their problem).

I had to press to receive compensation for the downgrade. I was offered an extra drink coupon and free breakfasts, which were a nice gesture but of no use to me given my schedule. They ultimately knocked a bit off my nightly rate, which made me feel somewhat better, but really what I wanted (traveling for business) was the nicer room. The staff was pleasant enough about the issue, but clearly wanted to "get it over with" in the most expedient fashion possible. The manager kept reminding me that he was willing to put me in these rooms "due to [my] gold status" as if providing me with a downgrade was somehow doing me a favor.

I went with the Cabana room at the recommendation of the night manager. The Cabana rooms are adequate by mid-tier hotel chain standards but in definite need of a refresh compared to the "main hotel" rooms (older tile floor as opposed to marble in the main hotel, older windows that make a whistling sound due to air pressure, etc.).

I want to like the Crown Plaza Cabana as it's convenient to a business destination for me and I stay there fairly often (5-6 times per year). Out of those, I'd say I've had some sort of issue with my visit around 50% of the time (false fire alarms going off during the night, room availability issues, item disappearing from lost-and-found). I'm honestly a very go-with-the-flow business traveler and not a "complainy" kind of review writer. But I'm going to think twice about staying at this particular hotel again, it's just gotten to be too much.< /review><Pics>None</Pics><Resp>None< /Resp>< gmap_id>

<response>None<//response><Rate>None</Rate>< text>
I have been staying at this property since December 2016 and from day one the staff has gone above and beyond for any request that I or my coworkers who have been staying since July of 2016. If there was anything that they either didn't know or had to clarify they made sure to get back to us. It's always been a pleasure dealing with the staff wether it was the front desk (Rose, Maritza) to the bar (Javier) all the way down to the shuttle driver (Steve). All of my stays have been without any complaints the rooms are cleaned daily the room service is quick along with the standard of food served in the restaurant/bar has been stellar. The only suggestion I have moving forward is that maybe the happy hour food menu or the full restaurant food menu could use a few new items. I have and will continue to encourage my coworkers to book at this location due to how well all the amenities and my experience has been thus far.</text>

I was surprised at the decor and cleanliness of the property for the price. It was a great value in that sense. However, the front desk service was terrible. I needed to check in early at 2 PM (preferably earlier) because I had to attend an event at 3. I called a week before my stay to ask for early check in. They told me to call the night before my stay. I called the night before my stay and was told that there was a good chance I could get early check in because the hotel was only at 70% capacity, however, they told me I needed to call the next morning to be sure. I called the following morning and I explained my situation and they told me that there were no rooms available and to call back at 11 AM. I called back at 11 AM and they took my number and told me that they would give me a call when my room was ready. I arrived at 2 PM because I needed to drop my car off before the event (although it would've been nice to settle in and get ready in my room beforehand), and my room was indeed ready. However, I DID NOT GET A CALL FROM ANYONE. POOR CUSTOMER SERVICE.< /Text>

<Pics>None<//Pics><name>PhilmGuy< /name>< Review>
The reservation was easy to make, and with the AAA discount (or was it the senior one?) it was a very reasonable price. When I arrived, I was told that my room had been upgraded, and my request for a quiet room on a high floor (made when reserving) had been taken care of. (Top floor, furthest room from elevators and ice machines.)

I haven't stayed here in decades, but it was perfectly comfortable and included everything I needed.

Oh, one thing... There was a poster in the elevator saying "the Beatles stayed here in '63." That was a year before their first US tour, and two years before they stayed at the Cabana. Close but no cigar! (I was in high school then, and we were all excited to have them in town!)< /Review>

< Review>
I have stayed at this property once or twice a month for the last 2 years and have always had an excellent stay. They are always accommodating to my requests (inside tower room, early check in, quiet floor), recognize me by name, provide free drink and breakfast coupons, upgrade my room type (as high as the several room suites free of charge), provide a free shuttle within a certain distance of the hotel, and the list goes on. During my last visit, I had arrived after a 13hr travel day - I was upgraded to an enormous suite, given a free drink and breakfast coupon and was left a plate of fresh fruit by the front office supervisor (Thanks Mr Khan!). The wireless internet is always free with excellent signal and the office/computer room is well stocked. The walls are well insulated so it is always quiet in my room - I never hear anything from adjoining rooms.
I have had to stay at the Sheraton Palo Alto when this property has been full and while the Sheraton has been extremely kind and welcoming (upgrading my rooms as well) and is closer to Stanford, the price is almost always higher and the Wifi is $10/day, which is really annoying and actually my biggest hangup about staying there.
The Crowne Plaza staff is fabulous and I look forward to my next stay; thanks to all at the Cabana!</Review>

I'll start with the not so great but please read the whole review. The not so great: the "poolside rooms" are a bit poorly maintained and outdated motel style rooms behind the main hotel. I booked this through my employers travel agency for a premium price per night so I expected a nice room but was not happy with the poolside room I was given. Now for the good: I did a quick Google and realized that I could in fact get the king suite in the tower for $5 more per night. I called the front desk and discussed my disappointment in my first room and they listened and apologized. Sadly the hotel was fully booked that night. Now for the amazing: I was staying there for 4 nights and on day 2 they transferred me into the king suite without giving me any guff or making me feel guilty in any way. They even sent a guy to move my bags over for me. They were so very nice and the new room is hands down my favorite hotel room I have ever had. It has a huge bedroom, a living room, and a deck with mountain views. Just outstanding. I am a service stickler and I would absolutely stay here again and again. Good work crowne!< /text>

< Review>
Crowne Plaza Hotel Palo Alto hit the mark for me as a well-run Hotel with very friendly staff and a safe, clean, slightly Bohemian feel that sets it apart from the run-of-the-mill corporate hotels where everything looks the same. The courtyard and pool in the rear are delightful, as are the large rooms with very good air temperature/quality and low ambient noise. I feel comfortable recommending the Palo Alto Crowne Plaza Hotel to my friends.< /Review>

< Text>
The hotel was sold out and had a lot of preteens there for some kind of event but it never stopped the service and attention to detail. We had a little bit of a long wait to check-in but the person at the counter was very apologetic and kept telling us they will be right with us. When we finally made it to the desk they again apologized and offered us water. The water came in handy as it was a smoldering day. After a few room changes we arrived back to a lovely note from Charles welcoming us to the hotel and apologizing once more for the delayed check in time. When we went to the desk to thank him we saw him running around to help other guests and staff so we talked to the lady host. She was nice and listened to us and we begin a conversation on my outfit that she loved because of its color. 
Everyone at this motel had smiles and stopped to ask how we were doing. I felt like the red carpet was rolled out for us.</Text>

< Rating>

< Review>
Stayed five nights for work and I've never been so happy to leave a hotel. It was 30 degrees Fahrenheit outside and my room was icy cold. After fighting with the heater all night (and not sleeping) thinking it was just my room I called and was told the broiler for part of the hotel was broken and no ETA on a fix and was given an extra blanket. I find out the next day from co-workers staying at the hotel there were space heaters available (no one offered me one) - some people even had two or three in their room. So I called the second night and was told one would be brought up. I waited quite a few hours and called again, I got a very un-inspired "sorry we ran out" with a promise to have one the next day. When I got back to my room after a long day I thankfully had one. The bathroom was still frozen but at least the bed area was warm enough to sleep.

Other than that the front desk staff was generally lackluster (one exception was when I checked in). The rest of the hotel was mostly freezing (we were meeting in rooms there and many had to wear coats).

The only bright spots was housekeeping, who did a great job, and the staff at the dining area. Maybe they should be running the place.</Review>

<Gmap_id>0x808fba78fa5aee1b:0xc1bcfddbc93e6091</Gmap_id><rating>None</rating>< review>
At first, as I looked for my room around the back of the hotel, I thought I was going to be disappointed, but upon entry, I found the room clean and well decorated. The huge bathroom housed a large closet that contained 2 suitcase stands (I don't think I've ever had 2 stands in 1 room); extra pillows and blankets - and all the normal amenities. The bathroom had 2 frosted glass panels that allowed a bit of light to shine through to the main part of the room. I loved the high back guest chair.
We stayed at the hotel due to the wedding of a friend - and the ceremony and reception were beautiful! Staff was helpful and friendly. The only hitch to the wedding ceremony is that the silky runner they laid down on the stone tiles for the bride and her bridesmaids to walk down caused a slippery situation for the girls who all wore high heeled shoes. That was not well thought out! Otherwise, I would highly recommend the hotel!< /review>

I am really disappointed and upset that I had to encounter Richard from the front desk on my wedding morning.

Prior to my stay at the hotel, I called in to ask if it would be OK for me to have a late check out on my wedding day since my bridesmaids and I had to get ready. The person who answered my call assured me that it would not be a problem.

On the day of my wedding, I walked over to the front desk to remind them that I would be checking out a little later. I encountered Richard, told him it was my wedding day and that I would be checking out late. Not only did he roll his eyes at me, he told me that I should have planned better and that this would have been a huge problem. I told him that someone told me that it was OK, but he kept talking over me - telling me that it wasn't OK and kept repeating that I should've planned better. Then he said he would have to charge me for an extra half day (which was fine). The only thing that made me upset and brought me to tears was when he kept blaming me for poor planning when I clearly stated that I had called in prior to make sure checking out late wasn't a problem.

I just hope that this doesn't happen to other people...especially on their wedding day. His unprofessionalism, rudeness, insensitivity, and mean attitude is not what I expected from the Crowne Plaza and has reflected very poorly on the hotel. I'm just sad that this had to happen to me on my wedding day.</text>

<Rating>None</Rating>< text>
Good Points - Hotel looks wonderful from the outside, nice lobby and staff are friendly. My room was spacious and the bed was comfortable. I had a suite with a view of the roof.

Negatives - there were several. Shuttle to Stanford was booked on the wrong day. We inquired as to the delay and told no problem they would be there any minute. 5 minutes later, the problem was discovered and we were late for our conference. 

Next plumbing issues. My bathroom had a great layout with 2 pedestal sinks. The pedestal sink on the left hand side, the cold faucet leaked. The right hand pedestal sink, the hot water faucet leaked. Last night of the stay, at approximately 3:45am I woke to the toilet cycling on and off. I discovered the toilet was slowly leaking. Needless to say, when I reported this, I was told it was a known intermittent problem and they would have a plumber look at it after I checked out. Since I had numerous towels, I tossed them on the floor to absorb the water and turned off the valve at the wall.< /text>

I'm also an IHG Rewards Member, but the only thing I got for this was a note offering me a free drink or some points, and two small pieces of chocolate on my 2nd day (nothing when arriving, and nothing on the other days).

Your experience will be based on who is working at the front desk and what room you have been assigned.

<date>1384819200000< /date><Rating>None<//Rating>< text>
I stayed at Crowne Plaza while attending a conference. The hotel is situated between silicon valley and Stanford university. Hence, plenty of thing to see. The public transport is relatively close, bus stops at the door, Caltrain is 15 minutes walk (San Antonio station). Hotel provide a shuttle that takes to to 5 mile radius for free which is superb.
The food at the hotel is sensational. I really engoyed it. There are also Chillie's, two Starbucks and other food retailers in close proximity.
The hotel was relatively old, but very clean and the room look as new. Staff were very helpful and kind too. :-)
Overall will recommend to everyone travelling to Palo Alto.</text>

< Text>
A very sensible choice of hotel, with a reasonable price, for the area. There is nothing here to dislike and a great deal to feel smug about given the price other hotels are charging nearby. The property and rooms are well maintained and comfortable. The staff are helpful and efficient. Wifi and parking were free, and there was a free shuttle service to the local area (which was not well advertised, but could be arranged from the front desk.)
If you pre-pay for breakfast, we found the 9 am cut-off time for the inclusive buffet far too early - we didn't make it once (who wants to rush to breakfast every morning when on vacation!). There was no refund for our unused vouchers and we were not told the timings on check-in. Aside from that, and the air-conditioning in the room which some might find a tad feeble, a very pleasing stay.< /Text>

< Text>
We checked in on a Thursday night. Our reservation had requested a room by the pool. We asked the person at the desk to look up our rewards number and she said she needed our address even though it was in the reservation. (Opportunity to think on her own.) The room key didn't work because the lock was broken or something. She called maintenance and asked them about any work being done in the room instead of moving us immediately. (Not the best thing to do in front of a guest.) We were then moved to another room but not told that it had 2 beds. We went back to ask for a room with 1 bed since that is what we reserved and wanted. Manager was called and moved us to a room with 1 bed. We weren't told it was a handicap accessible room. The shower came to our chin so we had to bend down to get our heads wet. No space in the bathroom to leave your toothbrush nor to hang your towel when you were done. Tried to order room service. They told us they'd have someone call us back. Several minutes later they called back to take the order. They got our order wrong and only sent up 1 order. The chicken was dry, overcooked and only slightly warm. The fries were cold. The air-conditioning in the room never got the room cold so we woke up sweating. We decided to check out the next morning only to be told that we would get charged a fee for early departure. As we told the staff member the problems we encountered, she said 'I do apologize' as though she was trained to just say it and not mean it. She then said I would have to wait to speak to her manager because he was in a meeting. I suggested she get him out of the meeting. The manager did try to help us but unfortunately his staff was incapable of thinking on their own and he made some poor decisions about our stay. We never got credit for the money we spent on our rewards either which adds to the frustration since we did have to pay despite all of the trouble. Overall it was a very bad experience after a 6 hour cross country flight.< /Text>

<Text>The great thing about this hotel is that it is set well back from noisy El Camino.

The hotel survey from IPSOS does not ask about noise levels in the room itself, just outside. Like most US h√¥tels, the air conditioning is very noisy, and the refrigerator, which is empty, goes on and off noisily all night long. I managed to turn the air conditioning off, though it still made some noise. In other h√¥tels I unplug the refrigerators, but that is not possible here. I was able to minimize the noise by turning the temperature control to the highest temperature setting.

Other than that, I like the style of the hotel and was able to find a good running trail nearby. (The bicycle trail into Palo Alto, if you look on Google earth.)</Text>< resp>

<date>1372636800000<//date><Rate>None</Rate><Text>I took a few days after a conference in San Francisco and moved down south a bit to the Palo Alto Cabana Crowne Plaza. From the photos it looked very nice, and usually when I just judge by the photos I'm disappointed. THIS HOTEL, however, was in no way a disappointment. It is excellent! The hotel is spacious and clean, beautiful setting. Parking lot was clean and easy to access. I was on the 8th floor and overlooked the pool and surrounding mountains. Very nice. Room was very clean and tidy. Bathroom was well stocked and cleaned every day. It was also a very quiet place. The pool area is the best. It is large, clean, very well kept. The pool was busy, yet quiet and nice to be at. There are shaded areas at the pool in case you want to avoid the sun. The restaurant was outstanding. I had breakfast there three of four days and it was very good. I had a later dinner there one night and the food was very tasty and cooked to order. From this property you are 10 minutes from Stanford and about 10 minutes from a very nice (and busy) "downtown" area of Palo Alto. Drive down there, find a place to park and just walk up and down the Avenue. So many things to visit. Overall this property is an A++. One more thing: All of the staff there were excellent. The housekeeping staff was very kind and considerate. The restaurant staff was "service first." The front desk staff was great and helpful. Overall, this is a very good place to stay. I will return, that's for sure.<//Text>< Pics>

<UserId.>115362898003952244191< /UserId.><Name>Elisa Lou</Name><time>1540269443670<//time><rating>2</rating><Text>I'm an IHG Platinum Elite member and stayed here for 1 night for business. It's not located in the best area, you'll have to drive a bit to get to some decent restaurants and shops. I would definitely prefer to stay in downtown PA.

This hotel does have many onsite amenities. I used the gym, which was spacious and has weights + benches + cardio machines, but no leg machines. Pool was there but didn't have chance to use it. Restaurant is open late, which is nice. There's also an area for buying convenience items like tylenol, nyquil, etc. which was useful.

Unfortunately the room quality was not good. I ended up with a room with a window that faces the outdoor walkway on the 2nd floor, meaning no privacy. I was too exhausted to ask for a room change since I checked in late in the evening, but this was definitely really disappointing. Because the window faced the outside, the sound proofness was also really bad. I could hear people parking and locking their cars while I was trying to sleep. I guess this is what it's like to stay in a motel room.

The ridiculous thing was that the room was priced at $445 a night for that week - not worth it. I understand they were hosting a conference during that time so there may have been a price increase, but it's still pretty unacceptable given the experience I had.

In conclusion, if you want to pay $445 a night for a motel experience then I guess you can stay here. Or maybe consider staying at a Marriott or SPG property, because at least they honor elite status.</Text>< pics>

<review>$250 Motel with lousy service. Don't stay here...

I stayed here on business travel and now I'm recommending that it be taken off their list of preferred locations.

The hotel is in need of repair and it does not resemble the ambiance that they try to portray on their site. The pool was closed even though the outdoor pools at neighboring locations was open. Throughout the hotel many things were only half repaired. It's as if repairs started and they ran out of funds.

There are garish lights positioned above every window that shine through the curtains. They would not turn these lights off but offered a curtain clip instead. The clips do not keep all of the light out of the room. I had enough light that I could still read my newspaper.

The hotel is an older building and the walls are thin. I could hear the elevators all night long. I could hear conversations in the hallways.

To top it all off they refused to help me with the billing situation. They were supposed to bill the employer and now they have billed both of us. They are argumentative and completely unwilling to try to help solve the situation.

The best part of my stay was the free shuttle service. The gentleman that drove the shuttle was also quite a good conversationalist.</review><rating>1</rating><pics>None< /pics><gmap_id>0x808fba78fa5aee1b:0xc1bcfddbc93e6091< /gmap_id><user_id>117399321471262427786</user_id>< user_name>

< review>
I wasn't expecting high-end comfort when I booked this reservation, but I do like a clean, relatively fresh-smelling room. The hotel exterior and lobby are presentable and relatively inviting. We were placed in one of the rooms that faced an outdoor second-story walkway, with viewing from the walkway into each of the rooms, which gave the room more of a motel feel than a hotel. I don't think all of the rooms are set up this way, but this is what we got. When we entered the room the smell was almost overwhelming. It really stunk, can't tell you of what, just an old musty smell, probably because the room had no outdoor-facing windows and was constantly closed up. It was gross.
